62A2A>(6/30/02 11:56:26 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2216.topic>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> A New Hope?</span><hr size=1> I played EverQuest for two years after its initial release, and quit due to the lack of roleplaying. I have returned several times since, only to find that the issue had not been addressed.<br>
<br>
Now, after being let-down by Asheron's Call, Anarchy Online, Dark Age of Camelot, Horizons, Archaean, Shadowbane, Atriarch, Warhammer Online, and Neverwinter Nights... I am now staring at my old EverQuest and Ruins of Kunark CDs... trying to resist the siren call... wondering if it is worth it....<br>
<br>
Is Firona Vie truly a roleplaying server? If I played Taranis Thilandrae, my Human-hating Elven Druid, would Half-Elves wonder about my stance toward them? If I played Aurindel, my High Elven Wizard who wishes the Wood Elves be outcast, would the response of some Wood Elves be violent? If I played Vehn Shataan, my Human Monk who dreads being a Human and admires the Elves to the point of obsession, would his own race call him mad and curse him on the streets of Qeynos?<br>
<br>
I am honestly disgusted by the representation of Elves with the new Shadows of Luclin models, but I fear that I may be able to look past them and perhaps grasp the magic that I had originally hoped Norrath would hold....<br>
<br>
Tell me... should I risk the possible waste of a monthly $10.00, or should I return to Neverwinter Nights -- which seems to dislike my beautiful and beloved Kyro II chipset? <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/uellestor.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ellestor</A> at: 6/30/02 11:58:19 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/udalninilvenorsh.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Dalninil Venorsh</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 41<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(7/1/02 12:14:49 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2216.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: A New Hope?</span><hr size=1> There are alot of folks that roleplay, there are some that don't. Fun is what you make of it. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/usydiafv.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Sydia FV</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 74<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(7/1/02 12:19:26 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2216.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: A New Hope?</span><hr size=1> The server is what you make of it.  There is a vast roleplaying community, normally denoted by the guild tag or quickly distinguished by the forms of speech used.  You still have what every other server in EQ has, however here you had better not outright disrespect the roleplay community ~ although it does happen and if you view the soapbox forum, i'm sure you'll get the idea.  The preferred term has been largely debated since the day Firiona Vie opened, as there are people who made the move for reasons other than to roleplay (different rule set).  <br>
<br>
As far as your story lines go, I'm sure there are people better versed in that area than me....i've nothing nice to say about it =)<br>
<br>
Those who stay here, probably do because we love the server ~ be it for roleplay, ruleset, whatever else have you =) and i like to think since the dawn of Firiona Vie all have grown to accept each other.....or at least try to...and when all else fails ignore /shrug <p>Sydia Vishious<Br>Enchanter 55<Br>
