<br>
Hearing that makes me miss my old (now disbanded) guild on Tallon Zek. Those higher in rank (who I spent most of my time round) were truly memorable characters when they did choose to roleplay.<br>
<br>
I am still wary of Shadows of Luclin, however... I really do hate the new Elf models, and they make me worry about what EverQuest 2 will be.<br>
<br>
Although, I also do not wish to play without Shadows of Luclin, because otherwise I have a hard time bearing the landscape and non-Elven models. I value roleplaying above all else in roleplaying games, but--oddly enough--graphics come second. The better the latter, the better I am with the former. For instance, I once started a conversation about a scar on the left arm of a Gnome I met in an old MUD. I have yet to be able to do this in a graphical game....<br>
<br>
[Shrugs] I will use the free 30-day account I received by e-mail last week, and connect to Luclin, and see what happens....<br>
<br>
Thank you all for your input. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ucylria.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Cylria</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 43<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(7/1/02 10:42:24 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2216.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: A New Hope?</span><hr size=1> I have a question for you, What would be an unacceptable roleplay environment to you? What has driven you away from so many MMRPGs?<br>
<br>
If you played Taranis, Cylria (half-elven) would wonder why you didn't like her, but this would be perfectly normal for her (you'd be the first anti-human wood elf she's met). I would understand that you are roleplaying though. So would most other people.<br>
<br>
You would need regular friends to pull off those three though. If you left groups when humans, or wood elves joined, poeple would understand that you're RPing, but you would still get a bad rep (but this is also realistic, and RP justified as your character wouldn't be trusted by friends/members of the unliked race). If you just grumbled at their presence in a group, most PLAYERS here wouldn't take offence, but their characters might. Just to be safe, though, you should probably send them a /tell to make sure they understand that you're just RPing.<br>
<br>
Also, even on FV, the game engine or environment hasn't really been changed. Thus NPC humans would like you until you killed your faction with them. A high-elf only guild would loose out in the high end game without any warriors. As would a wood elf/ogre/half-elf/etc... guild (with no clerics). Anything releted to the engine itself will be the same as you remeber (Except for No-Drop and Trivial Loot code). It's the players that make this a role-play server.<br>
<br>
Cylria <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/usmallcutepuppy.showPublicProfile?language=EN>smallcutepuppy</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 379<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(7/1/02 10:53:37 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2216.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: A New Hope?</span><hr size=1> You can use Luclin and just turn off the elf models if they're the only ones that bother you. I still don't care much for the new Iksar models; but I leave them turned on anyway just because the poly count is so much higher than the old ones. I can deal with my turtle head in exchange for actually having fingers, heh. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=fyresturm>Fyresturm</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 26<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(7/1/02 11:01:24 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2216.topic&index=10>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.mikkonen.org/jani/fyresturm2.png WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: A New Hope?</span><hr size=1> Well, there is definetly More(TM) roleplaying than on other servers. Allthou, cant say to what extend since my experience is only from Morell Thule and also, few years back.<br>
<br>
But anyway, you can and will find people that do roleplay and if you do, some, not most will respect it and go along even if they dont be ic first when you meet them. (atleast, this is what i've noticed)<br>
<br>
And btw, its not 10.00$ anymore, they raised the fee's a bit while back. Was it something like 12.95$ or ?<br>
