 <p>Fyresturm Alebreath,<br> Tapiolan Sankarit<br
<img src="http://www.mikkonen.org/jani/tapiola.jpg" alt="Tapiolan Sankarit"></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ukrazakthule.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Krazak Thule</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 189<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(7/1/02 11:18:25 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2216.topic&index=11>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Pros and Cons</span><hr size=1> Maybe what I will write here will make sense. Maybe it won't....<br>
<br>
<br>
There are a number of things that irritate me about Everquest. In fact, my list of cons is much larger than my list of pros.<br>
<br>
So why do I play EQ after I've long since abandon other games? <br>
<br>
Because the few pros in EQ have so much weight to them... <br>
<br>
What it comes down to for me is friendships and large group events. No other game, anywhere, gives you what EQ does. The ability to clear a plane with 24+ people. The ability to attack numerous dragons with large raid forces. The chance to work together as a team and win!<br>
<br>
Sidebar: I love dragons. Other games that have come out have purposely avoided putting dragons in their world for a variety of reasons (designers don't personally like them, or they don't want to clone EQ, or whatever). Me, I love dragons. And the chance to fight so many different types of dragons, and to have them be BIG encounters... is very appealing to me. <br>
<br>
But back to the main idea: Why do I keep playing EQ? <br>
<br>
People and events. I've enjoyed the people I've met playing this game. I've enjoyed my time playing EQ, even if the game itself often drives me mad. <br>
<br>
In the end, the friendships I make, and the events I've participated in, completely outweigh anything else. <br>
<br>
<br>
-Krazak Thule <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/utuppentangledroots.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Tuppen Tangledroots</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://webpages.marshall.edu/~parsons6/icon.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 29<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(7/1/02 11:56:37 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2216.topic&index=12>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://webpages.marshall.edu/~parsons6/tupsface.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Pros and Cons</span><hr size=1> Krazak,<br>
