Firiona Vie</b></font><br></font></p>
</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/uellestor.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ellestor</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 9<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(7/1/02 12:27:21 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2216.topic&index=13>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Pros and Cons</span><hr size=1> The primary Pros that would bring me back to EverQuest for more than this 30-day trial would be:<br>
<br>
1) Atmosphere<br>
2) Community<br>
3) More Atmosphere<br>
<br>
I simply love sitting under a large tree in the Greater Faydark with my Bard companion, Delanie, and listening to her music -- my Druid making stories out of her music for her. The moments are priceless.<br>
<br>
Then again, I also remember my stereotypical Dark Elf Necromancer killing High Elf maidens on the roads of the East Commonlands, only to be ambushed by a group of her unusual Halfling friends... and killing them, too.<br>
<br>
Ah... missed days of glory....<br>
<br>
Ahem.<br>
<br>
